**[1863, 06-12] Ms.A.9.2.31.65**

MWC to Anne Greene Chapman

War etc.

Praises black soldiers. “Negroes as {u}soldiers{/u} will save our
territory. … The negroes as {u}citizens{/u} will save our institutions.
They are buying the confiscated lands of Govt & will all be in their
places as {u}voters{/u}, at the end of the war, thus saving us from the
serious imputation of denying our great dogma of government by the
consent of the governed.{u} {/u}


